WEBVTT

00:11.560 --> 00:14.452
Hey... jacket?

00:14.491 --> 00:16.140
Or no jacket?

00:16.165 --> 00:18.971
- Jacket.
- Right. The two of us always wore jackets.

00:18.996 --> 00:20.996
We never hung out without jackets.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.628
- Dad?
- Natural waist, or sagging?

00:23.667 --> 00:25.792
Sagging, definitely.

00:25.834 --> 00:27.079
<i>Dad was nervous.</i>

00:27.134 --> 00:29.742
<i>Nervous about reuniting
with his best friend Noah.</i>

00:29.790 --> 00:31.148
<i>But he didn't have to be.</i>

00:31.204 --> 00:32.573
<i>They were old friends.</i>

00:32.607 --> 00:36.401
Come on, dad.
You guys are like these two.

00:36.439 --> 00:37.914
Who... Simon & Garfunkel?

00:37.959 --> 00:39.023
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

00:39.070 --> 00:41.257
Sure, life happens,
and you go your separate ways.

00:41.326 --> 00:45.359
But when you reunite,
it's like time stands still

00:45.427 --> 00:47.581
and you pick up right where you left off

00:47.650 --> 00:49.700
and make beautiful music together,

00:49.770 --> 00:52.026
according to Wikipedia.

00:52.093 --> 00:54.966
Right. Right where we left off.

00:55.035 --> 00:57.804
<i>The only thing was,</i>
<i>neither Simon nor Garfunkel</i>

00:57.872 --> 01:00.504
<i>had ever spent 80 days</i>
<i>seeking inpatient treatment</i>

01:00.573 --> 01:05.291
<i>for anger issues... at least</i>
<i>not according to Wikipedia.</i>

01:05.360 --> 01:07.443
[ Buzzer ]

01:12.334 --> 01:14.288
[ Gate clangs ]

01:15.054 --> 01:17.788
Free at last, buddy!
[ Laughs ]

01:17.858 --> 01:19.703
- Free at last! Whoo!
- Aah!

01:19.772 --> 01:22.678
Oh, what? I was just going in
for the high five.

01:22.747 --> 01:24.011
High fives aren't scary.

01:24.081 --> 01:26.644
High fives are 'cause
something awesome happened.

01:26.713 --> 01:28.764
There you go.

01:29.411 --> 01:32.325
I'm sorry. I just... I'm...

01:32.372 --> 01:34.286
- A little shell-shocked.
- Yeah.

01:34.318 --> 01:36.540
Right, I... I completely understand.

01:36.608 --> 01:38.249
But you're out.

01:39.111 --> 01:41.804
And you're leaving all that behind you.

01:41.873 --> 01:43.445
Right?

01:43.514 --> 01:45.980
We're both wearing jackets.
A new day is dawning.

01:46.035 --> 01:48.402
- Am I right?
- Right.

01:48.473 --> 01:49.940
- Right, so give me a pound!
- Aah!

01:50.010 --> 01:52.197
Okay. No... no pound.

01:52.267 --> 01:53.838
<i>So far, the reunion was</i>

01:53.908 --> 01:57.052
<i>a little more "Troubled Water"</i>
<i>than "Homeward Bound."</i>

01:57.121 --> 02:01.462
Wow, so, you're telling me
it's not even an elective.

02:01.532 --> 02:03.650
Correct. It's a class required
for graduation.

02:03.719 --> 02:07.752
Uh, but how does senior tanning
enrich students academically?

02:07.823 --> 02:08.984
It doesn't.

02:09.053 --> 02:12.061
It enriches our yearbook aesthetically.

02:12.129 --> 02:13.906
See, this is exactly
what's wrong with Chatswin.

02:13.976 --> 02:16.504
There is way too much
emphasis on aesthetics.

02:16.574 --> 02:20.539
We should be studying Descartes,
not De La Renta.

02:21.015 --> 02:23.520
But that is a super-cute De La Renta.

02:23.606 --> 02:25.325
Thanks.

02:25.394 --> 02:28.394
Sync and corrections by atrn97g
for www.add9c7ed.com

02:28.440 --> 02:31.516
Alih Jey: ♪ Last night I had
a pleasant nightmare ♪

02:31.578 --> 02:35.578
Suburgatory 3x05 - Blame it on the Rainstick
Original air date February 26, 2014

02:35.651 --> 02:37.462
♪ Da, da, da, da ♪

02:37.533 --> 02:38.659
Dalia: Okay.

02:38.728 --> 02:40.370
Hey, seniors.

02:40.437 --> 02:42.077
Now, as you all know,

02:42.147 --> 02:44.471
I'll be overseeing the tanning unit,

02:44.540 --> 02:47.206
as well as all subsequent field trips

02:47.275 --> 02:49.770
wherein we will be tanning your unit.

02:49.840 --> 02:53.880
Curious... who here knows
the proper tanning form?

02:53.936 --> 02:55.406
If your hand's not in the air,

02:55.475 --> 02:57.970
don't despair, as I will be
going over all that.

02:58.038 --> 03:01.012
Now, those of you
with more junk in the trunk,

03:01.082 --> 03:03.985
you will need to be vigilant
about performing

03:04.055 --> 03:06.891
a maneuver known
as the butt-cheek check.

03:06.963 --> 03:09.662
And if you're white as chalk like Tessa,

03:09.730 --> 03:11.370
you need to start slow.

03:11.440 --> 03:14.675
If you drop a cracker into a fire,

03:14.730 --> 03:18.832
it just burns, and so, too, will you.

03:18.901 --> 03:20.882
- Yes.
- I have to go pee.

03:21.742 --> 03:23.655
Okay.

03:24.644 --> 03:26.787
<i>Senior tanning?</i>

03:26.842 --> 03:30.021
<i>The more I thought about it,</i>
<i>the more I made peace with it.</i>

03:30.090 --> 03:32.755
<i>It wasn't something I saw</i>
<i>myself doing pre-Chatswin,</i>

03:32.826 --> 03:35.367
<i>but maybe it was time to surprise myself</i>

03:35.398 --> 03:37.790
<i>and for the first time ever...</i>

03:38.443 --> 03:40.404
<i>ditch school.</i>

03:44.318 --> 03:48.009
This is nice...
Good, old-fashioned hang.

03:48.079 --> 03:50.916
Hang sesh.

03:53.378 --> 03:57.346
Just a couple of bros
enjoying the sound of silence.

03:57.394 --> 03:59.925
Silence, yeah.

03:59.993 --> 04:02.260
[ Biederman panting ]

04:02.323 --> 04:04.713
I, uh... I... I notice...

04:04.766 --> 04:08.023
- you're wearing glasses.
- Yeah.

04:08.088 --> 04:11.266
I don't recall
you ever wearing glasses before.

04:11.287 --> 04:13.205
No.

04:14.372 --> 04:16.772
Something happen to your eyes?

04:16.797 --> 04:19.149
I wasn't seeing clearly.

04:19.206 --> 04:20.877
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:20.947 --> 04:23.533
Okay. Noah...

04:23.586 --> 04:25.878
what did they do to you in there?

04:25.945 --> 04:27.483
The A.C. isn't on,

04:27.527 --> 04:29.647
and you haven't complained once
about the temperature.

04:29.672 --> 04:31.273
I haven't heard a single snide comment

04:31.278 --> 04:34.278
about how uncomfortable
the couch is or the dog smell,

04:34.325 --> 04:35.752
which I know you hate.

04:35.792 --> 04:39.310
But I don't hate. Not anymore.

04:39.380 --> 04:40.575
Sorry, I'm not buying it.

04:40.646 --> 04:44.007
There are way too many things
that enrage you.

04:44.062 --> 04:46.363
- Not anymore.
- Yeah?

04:46.801 --> 04:48.266
Pomegranates.

04:48.335 --> 04:49.676
Worth the effort.

04:49.723 --> 04:51.874
Ted Danson dating Whoopi Goldberg.

04:51.944 --> 04:55.123
The heart... wants what it wants.

04:55.191 --> 04:57.229
The sequel to "Bring It On."

04:57.277 --> 05:01.333
Was entitled "Bring It On Again"
and aptly so.

05:01.398 --> 05:03.448
It got the job done.

05:03.519 --> 05:05.959
<i>While George was getting</i>
<i>his first taste of the new Noah</i>

05:06.013 --> 05:09.363
<i>I was tasting freedom,</i>
<i>and it was delicious.</i>

05:09.432 --> 05:11.381
[ <i> Up-tempo music playing</i> ]

05:11.450 --> 05:13.432
[ Drum beating ]

05:13.501 --> 05:15.995
[ "Moth's Wings" plays ]

05:22.238 --> 05:25.159
<i>In Manhattan, parks were mostly</i>
<i>for buying drugs</i>

05:25.217 --> 05:27.464
<i>and public urination, but in Chatswin,</i>

05:27.511 --> 05:29.459
<i>it seemed like the parks</i>
<i>were used for...</i>

05:29.529 --> 05:31.168
<i>something else.</i>

05:36.948 --> 05:40.638
♪ Dear friend, as you know ♪

05:41.059 --> 05:44.100
♪ Your flowers are withering ♪

05:44.795 --> 05:49.026
♪ Your mother's gone insane ♪

05:49.068 --> 05:52.541
♪ And your leaves have drifted away ♪

05:52.597 --> 05:54.448
♪ You're just like your father ♪
What's going on in here?!

05:54.495 --> 05:56.853
I don't know... performance art,
some stupid band.

05:56.924 --> 05:58.949
♪ Buried deep under the water ♪
I'm out. I got zumba in half an hour.

05:58.982 --> 06:00.369
♪ You're resting on your laurels ♪

06:00.433 --> 06:02.528
<i>Whatever it was, it was
incredibly un-Chatswin-like.</i>

06:02.529 --> 06:05.914
<i>And by that, I mean it was amazing.</i>

06:05.981 --> 06:09.332
♪ Come lay with me on the ground ♪

06:09.992 --> 06:12.212
Whoo!

06:12.282 --> 06:15.017
Whoo!

06:15.085 --> 06:18.409
Wow, that was just, like... wow!

06:18.472 --> 06:22.298
- Thanks.
- And you guys get so... sweaty.

06:22.368 --> 06:25.835
- Yeah, we do. - Just, like, a lot of
sweat in a really short period of time.

06:25.891 --> 06:28.420
It's not that hot in here... impressive.

06:28.490 --> 06:30.745
- I'm Caris.
- Tessa.

06:30.814 --> 06:33.540
I couldn't help but notice that
our music seemed to move you.

06:33.611 --> 06:36.173
It was like you were singing
what I was feeling.

06:36.219 --> 06:37.532
Isn't it amazing?

06:37.579 --> 06:41.611
People wander across
each other's paths for a reason.

06:41.674 --> 06:44.681
And I bet there's a reason
you wandered across ours.

06:44.750 --> 06:46.732
Yeah, 'cause I cut school.

06:46.802 --> 06:49.126
Guys, this is Tessa.

06:49.196 --> 06:54.829
Tessa, this is Carol, Tommy,
Lonny, Dommy, Nonny, Konny,

06:54.868 --> 06:59.649
Bahammy, Mikey, Likey,
Tikey, Sikey, Moop, Meep,

06:59.697 --> 07:02.228
Nimmy, Dimmy, and Luke.

07:02.504 --> 07:04.994
We're a group of musical nomads.

07:05.034 --> 07:09.238
We live together, and we travel
wherever the rhythm brings us.

07:09.306 --> 07:11.575
And it brought you to Chatswin?

07:11.622 --> 07:15.309
[ Laughs ]
I think it brought us to you.

